This paper is about distant supervision and relation extraction, which are both topics in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Within cs.CL, the paper focuses on machine learning techniques for NLP, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with attention mechanisms, which are a popular topic in NLP research, and may suggest sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
